According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Licensed Sports Apparel & Merchandise market was valued at USD 36,150 million in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 38,720 million in 2025 to USD 60,490 million by 2034, registering a CAGR of 7.4% during the forecast period. The market is expanding steadily as global sports fandom continues to rise, supported by increasing consumer spending on official team merchandise, growing digital engagement, and expanding licensing partnerships between sports organizations and leading apparel brands. The popularity of professional sports leagues, international tournaments, and athlete-driven branding is encouraging consumers to purchase authentic licensed products that reflect their loyalty and personal identity. At the same time, advancements in e-commerce, digital retail experiences, and premium product offerings are creating new opportunities for market participants across both developed and emerging economies.
